Converting gallons to cups (since it’s more common for bottled waters):

\( \text{Volume per Bottle} = \frac{128}{8}\,\text{cups/gal} \times 16.9\,\text{fl.\,oz./cup} \)

\( \text{Volume per Bottle} = 32\,\text{cups/gal} \times 16.9\,\text{fl.\,oz./cup} \)

\( \text{Volume per Bottle} = 544\,\text{fl.\,oz./gal} \times 16.9\,\text{fl.\,oz./cup} \)

\( \text{Volume per Bottle} = 9184\,\text{fl.\,oz./cup} \)

Thus, the volume of one bottle is approximately \( 91.84\,\text{fluid ounces} \).
